
This one was a complete accadent. So I wrote down what I did.

Two breakfast sausages, chopped into bite size bits.
Two slices of bacon, chopped up about the same.
Fry 'till about 1/2 cooked.
Toss in a handful of chopped green onions.
Fry some more.
Mix 2 eggs, 1 chopped up slice American, and 1 chopped up slice of cheddar cheese, in cup or bowl.
Toss a second handful of chopped green onions, into the pan.
Fry for a bit longer.
Pour the egg & cheese mixture into the pan.
Grind in some pepper. NO salt! I'll be salty enough without.
Fry 'till the eggs are done as desired.
Serve - Enjoy!